div.p: PTRACE_PEEKDATA returns a long (8 bytes). If the read fails, it returns -1. However, 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF (-1) is also a valid bit pattern in tracee memory. Code Standard: Must differentiate between "Data is -1" and "Call Failed".

g.text: c long ptrace(enum __ptrace_request request, pid_t pid, void *addr, void *data);
